pageContext.quote: And then you realize that this area of stuff that you don’t know is almost infinite. So, you realize that learning in programming — it cannot be completed. Not even close. You just have to pick like, a path inside of it and go slowly and just grow and compare yourself to the person that you were yesterday. That feeling of, “Oh my god, there is so much that I don’t know,” that feeling will not go away by learning more. It will grow — to a point where you just realize, “Oh...uh...OK.”
